Math Functions
command -v can be used to check if the command is present or not also 
[] are not needed if you are not using test/check condition in the if 
you have to use
expr num1 <operator> num2
expr num1 \* num2 because * is the special purpose in bash
ls means list storage
echo $SHELL to check the name of shell
which shell to check the location of shell is installed in
#! --> known as shebang
variables defined on the terminals are only saved for that session
the variables named with upper case are environment variables also known as system variables
You can find system/environment variables by typing env
